The paper discusses unsupervised learning of disentangled representations, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of Wasserstein total correlation in variational autoencoder and Wasserstein autoencoder settings. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
